ETAPE 3

1.
find -type f

2.
find -type f |grep le

3.
find /usr/include -maxdepth 1 -type f
find /usr/include -maxdepth 1 -type d

4.
cat /usr/include/stdio.h | wc
The size of the file is around 32K (du -h /usr/include/stdio.h) which is linked to the number of caracters.
The exact size of the file (31365 bytes) is the same as the number of caracters (ls -l  /usr/include/stdio.h)
 
5.
find /usr/include -maxdepth 1 -type f | wc -l
find /usr/include -type f | wc -l

6.
find /usr/include -type f -exec grep "^#" {} \; | wc -l

7.
find -type f |grep [^a-z]le[^a-z]
